name: Auratouched Mage
text: When Auratouched Mage enters the battlefield, search your library for an Aura card that could enchant it. If Auratouched Mage is still on the battlefield, put that Aura card onto the battlefield attached to it. Otherwise, reveal the Aura card and put it into your hand. Then shuffle your library.

name: Bathe in Light
text: Radiance — Choose a color. Target creature and each other creature that shares a color with it gain protection from the chosen color until end of turn.
flavor: "Truth shines even in darkness. Those who march on the side of truth walk always in righteous light."

name: Benevolent Ancestor
text: Defender (This creature can't attack.)\n{T}: Prevent the next 1 damage that would be dealt to target creature or player this turn.
flavor: Although the door is flimsy and the lock pathetically small, Josuri's family never fears the night outside.

name: Blazing Archon
text: Flying\nCreatures can't attack you.
flavor: "Through the haze of battle I saw the glint of sun on golden mane, the sheen of glory clad in mail, and I dropped my sword and wept at the idiocy of war."\n—Dravin, Gruul deserter

name: Boros Fury-Shield
text: Prevent all combat damage that would be dealt by target attacking or blocking creature this turn. If {R} was spent to cast Boros Fury-Shield, it deals damage to that creature's controller equal to the creature's power.

name: Caregiver
text: {W}, Sacrifice a creature: Prevent the next 1 damage that would be dealt to target creature or player this turn.
flavor: "The guilds each believe its way is right, but their ways only bring blood to Ravnica's streets and tears to Ravnica's families."

name: Chant of Vitu-Ghazi
text: Convoke (Your creatures can help cast this spell. Each creature you tap while casting this spell pays for {1} or one mana of that creature's color.)\nPrevent all damage that would be dealt by creatures this turn. You gain life equal to the damage prevented this way.

name: Concerted Effort
text: At the beginning of each upkeep, creatures you control gain flying until end of turn if a creature you control has flying. The same is true for fear, first strike, double strike, landwalk, protection, trample, and vigilance.

name: Conclave Equenaut
text: Convoke (Your creatures can help cast this spell. Each creature you tap while casting this spell pays for {1} or one mana of that creature's color.)\nFlying
flavor: Equenauts are the seeds of the Conclave, scattered on the four winds, searching for new places to take root.

name: Conclave Phalanx
text: Convoke (Your creatures can help cast this spell. Each creature you tap while casting this spell pays for {1} or one mana of that creature's color.)\nWhen Conclave Phalanx enters the battlefield, you gain 1 life for each creature you control.

name: Conclave's Blessing
text: Convoke (Your creatures can help cast this spell. Each creature you tap while casting this spell pays for {1} or one mana of that creature's color.)\nEnchant creature\nEnchanted creature gets +0/+2 for each other creature you control.

name: Courier Hawk
text: Flying, vigilance
flavor: The Orzhov started using hawks as messengers in order to bypass the many toll roads and bridges that dot Ravnica. Soon the service became one of their most profitable businesses.

name: Devouring Light
text: Convoke (Your creatures can help cast this spell. Each creature you tap while casting this spell pays for {1} or one mana of that creature's color.)\nExile target attacking or blocking creature.
flavor: Into the light the good are welcomed, and with the light the evil are banished.

name: Divebomber Griffin
text: Flying\n{T}, Sacrifice Divebomber Griffin: Divebomber Griffin deals 3 damage to target attacking or blocking creature.
flavor: Justice flies swiftly on angry wings.

name: Dromad Purebred
text: Whenever Dromad Purebred is dealt damage, you gain 1 life.
flavor: "I have seen much from the back of my dromad, most of it terribly wrong. The more I see, the more I am convinced of the rightness of my path."\n—Heruj, Selesnya initiate

name: Faith's Fetters
text: Enchant permanent\nWhen Faith's Fetters enters the battlefield, you gain 4 life.\nEnchanted permanent's activated abilities can't be activated unless they're mana abilities. If enchanted permanent is a creature, it can't attack or block.

name: Festival of the Guildpact
text: Prevent the next X damage that would be dealt to you this turn.\nDraw a card.
flavor: Everyone knows that violence at the Festival brings the worst of luck, so for at least one day a year arms are laid down in favor of brimming goblets.

name: Flickerform
text: Enchant creature\n{2}{W}{W}: Exile enchanted creature and all Auras attached to it. At the beginning of the next end step, return that card to the battlefield under its owner's control. If you do, return the other cards exiled this way to the battlefield under their owners' control attached to that creature.

name: Gate Hound
text: Creatures you control have vigilance as long as Gate Hound is enchanted.
flavor: "Ditri, I leave this checkpoint in your capable teeth."\n—Kitov, nightguard patrol

name: Ghosts of the Innocent
text: If a source would deal damage to a creature or player, it deals half that damage, rounded down, to that creature or player instead.
flavor: "Ma said we should offer up blini-cakes and salt to the good ones, but I get that chill up my spine and just shut the door."\n—Otak, Tin Street shopkeep

name: Hour of Reckoning
text: Convoke (Your creatures can help cast this spell. Each creature you tap while casting this spell pays for {1} or one mana of that creature's color.)\nDestroy all nontoken creatures.
flavor: "Ravnica, like a hedge, must be pruned, leaving only leaves of verdant uniformity."\n—Niszka, Selesnya evangel

name: Hunted Lammasu
text: Flying\nWhen Hunted Lammasu enters the battlefield, target opponent puts a 4/4 black Horror creature token onto the battlefield.
flavor: The lammasu ruled the velds before the city grew. Now they roam Ravnica's skies, but their ancient enemies have not forgotten them.

name: Leave No Trace
text: Radiance — Destroy target enchantment and each other enchantment that shares a color with it.
flavor: The magic of the Boros patrols the streets even when their soldiers do not.

name: Light of Sanction
text: Prevent all damage that would be dealt to creatures you control by sources you control.
flavor: The Legion looks after its own.

name: Loxodon Gatekeeper
text: Artifacts, creatures, and lands your opponents control enter the battlefield tapped.
flavor: The gatekeepers are so fastidious that even the winds must wait to pass.

name: Nightguard Patrol
text: First strike, vigilance
flavor: "The Wojek defend the laws. We defend the people."

name: Oathsworn Giant
text: Vigilance\nOther creatures you control get +0/+2 and have vigilance.
flavor: The town stands on his ancestors' former burial grounds. Even with the graves long gone, he continues his determined vigil.

name: Sandsower
text: Tap three untapped creatures you control: Tap target creature.
flavor: It drifts through the streets as a breeze of collective sighs, wilting the bustle with dreams and heavy eyelids.

name: Screeching Griffin
text: Flying\n{R}: Target creature can't block Screeching Griffin this turn.
flavor: They were master fishers, but their seas are now the streets and their catch, the goblins that run pell-mell from the screeching in the sky.

name: Seed Spark
text: Destroy target artifact or enchantment. If {G} was spent to cast Seed Spark, put two 1/1 green Saproling creature tokens onto the battlefield.
flavor: "If you ask me, those root-lovers value mindless dogma over progress."\n—Trivaz, Izzet mage

name: Suppression Field
text: Activated abilities cost {2} more to activate unless they're mana abilities.
flavor: The most feared of Azorius punishments is to be freed—sent back out into the world, stripped of all magical defenses.

name: Three Dreams
text: Search your library for up to three Aura cards with different names, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then shuffle your library.
flavor: "Choose one to heal, one to harm, and one to grant you the prudence to use them."\n—Miotri, auratouched mage

name: Twilight Drover
text: Whenever a creature token leaves the battlefield, put a +1/+1 counter on Twilight Drover.\n{2}{W}, Remove a +1/+1 counter from Twilight Drover: Put two 1/1 white Spirit creature tokens with flying onto the battlefield.

name: Veteran Armorer
text: Other creatures you control get +0/+1.
flavor: "Give me a sword and I'll kill a few enemies. But give me a hammer and a fiery forge, and I'll turn the tide of battle."

name: Votary of the Conclave
text: {2}{G}: Regenerate Votary of the Conclave.
flavor: An ageless order, the votaries receive the gift of rejuvenation from the temple gardens they guard.

name: Wojek Apothecary
text: Radiance — {T}: Prevent the next 1 damage that would be dealt to target creature and each other creature that shares a color with it this turn.
flavor: "A few arrows aren't enough to pierce your faith, soldier. You'll be back on the battlefield by sun's dawn."

name: Wojek Siren
text: Radiance — Target creature and each other creature that shares a color with it get +1/+1 until end of turn.
flavor: It is the call to arms, the call to fury, the call to blood.

name: Belltower Sphinx
text: Flying\nWhenever a source deals damage to Belltower Sphinx, that source's controller puts that many cards from the top of his or her library into his or her graveyard.

name: Cerulean Sphinx
text: Flying\n{U}: Cerulean Sphinx's owner shuffles it into his or her library.
flavor: "About the sphinx, I have mixed feelings. Their wisdom I crave, but their secrecy I can't tolerate."\n—Szadek

name: Compulsive Research
text: Target player draws three cards. Then that player discards two cards unless he or she discards a land card.
flavor: "Four parts molten bronze, yes . . . one part frozen mercury, yes, yes . . . but then what?"

name: Convolute
text: Counter target spell unless its controller pays {4}.
flavor: The words came to the sorcerer's lips but refused to budge any further.

name: Copy Enchantment
text: You may have Copy Enchantment enter the battlefield as a copy of any enchantment on the battlefield.
flavor: Simic mages create redundant backups of their experiments to reduce the consequences of catastrophe.

name: Dizzy Spell
text: Target creature gets -3/-0 until end of turn.\nTransmute {1}{U}{U} ({1}{U}{U}, Discard this card: Search your library for a card with the same converted mana cost as this card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then shuffle your library. Transmute only as a sorcery.)

name: Drake Familiar
text: Flying\nWhen Drake Familiar enters the battlefield, sacrifice it unless you return an enchantment to its owner's hand.
flavor: "Falconry? A fine sport I suppose, if you're attracted to the frailty of birds."\n—Trivaz, Izzet mage

name: Dream Leash
text: Enchant permanent\nYou can't choose an untapped permanent as Dream Leash's target as you cast Dream Leash.\nYou control enchanted permanent.
flavor: The tendrils of sorcery find easy purchase on the soft underbelly of dreams.

name: Drift of Phantasms
text: Defender (This creature can't attack.)\nFlying\nTransmute {1}{U}{U} ({1}{U}{U}, Discard this card: Search your library for a card with the same converted mana cost as this card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then shuffle your library. Transmute only as a sorcery.)

name: Ethereal Usher
text: {U}, {T}: Target creature can't be blocked this turn.\nTransmute {1}{U}{U} ({1}{U}{U}, Discard this card: Search your library for a card with the same converted mana cost as this card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then shuffle your library. Transmute only as a sorcery.)

name: Eye of the Storm
text: Whenever a player casts an instant or sorcery card, exile it. Then that player copies each instant or sorcery card exiled with Eye of the Storm. For each copy, the player may cast the copy without paying its mana cost.

name: Flight of Fancy
text: Enchant creature\nWhen Flight of Fancy enters the battlefield, draw two cards.\nEnchanted creature has flying.
flavor: The view from above is an inspiration to the newly winged.

name: Flow of Ideas
text: Draw a card for each Island you control.
flavor: "A system to direct the flow of Ravnica's entire water supply? Thinking a bit small, aren't we?"\n—Trivaz, Izzet mage

name: Followed Footsteps
text: Enchant creature\nAt the beginning of your upkeep, put a token that's a copy of enchanted creature onto the battlefield.
flavor: Æther can turn a footprint into a blueprint.

name: Grayscaled Gharial
text: Islandwalk (This creature can't be blocked as long as defending player controls an Island.)
flavor: Each tooth carries enough bacteria to kill a person in a day or two. But then, gharials do have 138 teeth.

name: Grozoth
text:
Defender (This creature can't attack.)
When Grozoth enters the battlefield, you may search your library for any number of cards that have converted mana cost 9, reveal them, and put them into your hand. If you do, shuffle your library.
{4}: Grozoth loses defender until end of turn.
Transmute {1}{U}{U} ({1}{U}{U}, Discard this card: Search your library for a card with the same converted mana cost as this card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then shuffle your library. Transmute only as a sorcery.)

name: Halcyon Glaze
text: Whenever you cast a creature spell, Halcyon Glaze becomes a 4/4 Illusion creature with flying in addition to its other types until end of turn.
flavor: "Earth to æther, window to wonder, stillness to the sky."\n—Glazing incantation

name: Hunted Phantasm
text: Hunted Phantasm can't be blocked.\nWhen Hunted Phantasm enters the battlefield, target opponent puts five 1/1 red Goblin creature tokens onto the battlefield.

name: Induce Paranoia
text: Counter target spell. If {B} was spent to cast Induce Paranoia, that spell's controller puts the top X cards of his or her library into his or her graveyard, where X is the spell's converted mana cost.

name: Lore Broker
text: {T}: Each player draws a card, then discards a card.
flavor: Lies are sold as often as truths—and used just as effectively.

name: Mark of Eviction
text: Enchant creature\nAt the beginning of your upkeep, return enchanted creature and all Auras attached to that creature to their owners' hands.
flavor: Tharashk the Bold suddenly wasn't himself. Or anyone else, for that matter.

name: Mnemonic Nexus
text: Each player shuffles his or her graveyard into his or her library.
flavor: True enlightenment comes not with a new thought, but with understanding of all the old ones.

name: Muddle the Mixture
text: Counter target instant or sorcery spell.\nTransmute {1}{U}{U} ({1}{U}{U}, Discard this card: Search your library for a card with the same converted mana cost as this card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then shuffle your library. Transmute only as a sorcery.)

name: Peel from Reality
text: Return target creature you control and target creature you don't control to their owners' hands.
flavor: When House Dimir's secrets are in danger of exposure, the guild takes drastic measures to cover its tracks.

name: Quickchange
text: Target creature becomes the color or colors of your choice until end of turn.\nDraw a card.
flavor: Most Ravnicans lead lives of desperate survival. Those who thrive are malleable enough to change with the ever-shifting politics of the guilds.

name: Remand
text: Counter target spell. If that spell is countered this way, put it into its owner's hand instead of into that player's graveyard.\nDraw a card.
flavor: "Well, at least all of that arm-waving and arcane babbling you did was impressive."

name: Snapping Drake
text: Flying
flavor: The irritable drakes are solitary nesters. Even brooding females barely contain the urge to attack their own young.

name: Spawnbroker
text: When Spawnbroker enters the battlefield, you may exchange control of target creature you control and target creature with power less than or equal to that creature's power an opponent controls.
flavor: "The trick isn't setting up the bad trade. It's making each side think it got the better deal."

name: Stasis Cell
text: Enchant creature\nEnchanted creature doesn't untap during its controller's untap step.\n{3}{U}: Attach Stasis Cell to target creature.
flavor: The Simic created the cells to preserve their experiments. The Azorius put the cells to use on the guilty.

name: Surveilling Sprite
text: Flying\nWhen Surveilling Sprite dies, you may draw a card.
flavor: Their natural curiosity, combined with a knack for trespassing, makes sprites excellent spies.

name: Tattered Drake
text: Flying\n{B}: Regenerate Tattered Drake.
flavor: "Drakes embody the worst of Ravnica: great potential, twisted by selfishness and greed."\n—Razia

name: Telling Time
text: Look at the top three cards of your library. Put one of those cards into your hand, one on top of your library, and one on the bottom of your library.
flavor: Mastery is achieved when "telling time" becomes "telling time what to do."

name: Terraformer
text: {1}: Choose a basic land type. Each land you control becomes that type until end of turn.
flavor: "This feels a little more like home."

name: Tidewater Minion
text: Defender (This creature can't attack.)\n{4}: Tidewater Minion loses defender until end of turn.\n{T}: Untap target permanent.

name: Tunnel Vision
text: Name a card. Target player reveals cards from the top of his or her library until the named card is revealed. If it is, that player puts the rest of the revealed cards into his or her graveyard and puts the named card on top of his or her library. Otherwise, the player shuffles his or her library.

name: Vedalken Dismisser
text: When Vedalken Dismisser enters the battlefield, put target creature on top of its owner's library.
flavor: "I crept up on him, quiet as a guttermouse. And then suddenly I found myself facedown in a latrine pit behind Tin Street Market."\n—Sirislav, Dimir spy

name: Vedalken Entrancer
text: {U}, {T}: Target player puts the top two cards of his or her library into his or her graveyard.
flavor: Their denial reaches far into your future.

name: Wizened Snitches
text: Flying\nPlayers play with the top card of their libraries revealed.
flavor: "Be careful what information you ask them to find, for it will likely be the subject of tale time at the alehouse."\n—Sirislav, Dimir spy

name: Zephyr Spirit
text: When Zephyr Spirit blocks, return it to its owner's hand.
flavor: A spiteful force exists on Ravnica that binds these ghosts to the land of the living but forbids them to touch it.

name: Blood Funnel
text: Noncreature spells you cast cost {2} less to cast.\nWhenever you cast a noncreature spell, counter that spell unless you sacrifice a creature.

name: Brainspoil
text: Destroy target creature that isn't enchanted. It can't be regenerated.\nTransmute {1}{B}{B} ({1}{B}{B}, Discard this card: Search your library for a card with the same converted mana cost as this card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then shuffle your library. Transmute only as a sorcery.)

name: Carrion Howler
text: Pay 1 life: Carrion Howler gets +2/-1 until end of turn.
flavor: They chase tirelessly after the bone-carts that speed along the streets of the Plague Quarter.

name: Clinging Darkness
text: Enchant creature\nEnchanted creature gets -4/-1.
flavor: There's an experience worse than blindness—it's the certainty that your vision is perfect and the horror that there's no world around you to see.

name: Dark Confidant
text: At the beginning of your upkeep, reveal the top card of your library and put that card into your hand. You lose life equal to its converted mana cost.
flavor: Greatness, at any cost.

name: Darkblast
text: Target creature gets -1/-1 until end of turn.\nDredge 3 (If you would draw a card, instead you may put exactly three cards from the top of your library into your graveyard. If you do, return this card from your graveyard to your hand. Otherwise, draw a card.)

name: Dimir House Guard
text: Fear (This creature can't be blocked except by artifact creatures and/or black creatures.)\nSacrifice a creature: Regenerate Dimir House Guard.\nTransmute {1}{B}{B} ({1}{B}{B}, Discard this card: Search your library for a card with the same converted mana cost as this card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then shuffle your library. Transmute only as a sorcery.)

name: Dimir Machinations
text: Look at the top three cards of target player's library. Exile any number of those cards, then put the rest back in any order.\nTransmute {1}{B}{B} ({1}{B}{B}, Discard this card: Search your library for a card with the same converted mana cost as this card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then shuffle your library. Transmute only as a sorcery.)

name: Disembowel
text: Destroy target creature with converted mana cost X.
flavor: "We thought we found the victim's clothes lumped in the street. As it turned out, it was the victim, insides sucked out—just a sack of skin and robes."\n—Agrus Kos

name: Empty the Catacombs
text: Each player returns all creature cards from his or her graveyard to his or her hand.
flavor: When the dead are laid to rest in Ravnica, it's usually just a nap.

name: Golgari Thug
text: When Golgari Thug dies, put target creature card from your graveyard on top of your library.\nDredge 4 (If you would draw a card, instead you may put exactly four cards from the top of your library into your graveyard. If you do, return this card from your graveyard to your hand. Otherwise, draw a card.)

name: Helldozer
text: {B}{B}{B}, {T}: Destroy target land. If that land was nonbasic, untap Helldozer.
flavor: Sometimes you go to hell, and sometimes hell comes to you.

name: Hex
text: Destroy six target creatures.
flavor: When killing five just isn't enough.

name: Hunted Horror
text: Trample\nWhen Hunted Horror enters the battlefield, target opponent puts two 3/3 green Centaur creature tokens with protection from black onto the battlefield.

name: Infectious Host
text: When Infectious Host dies, target player loses 2 life.
flavor: "Lost man, dead man, knocking on the door.\nCankerman, soreman, knock no more."\n—Ravnican children's rhyme

name: Keening Banshee
text: Flying\nWhen Keening Banshee enters the battlefield, target creature gets -2/-2 until end of turn.
flavor: Her cold wail echoes in the alleys and under-eaves, finding the unfortunate and turning their blood to ice.

name: Last Gasp
text: Target creature gets -3/-3 until end of turn.
flavor: "Allow me a moment to catch your breath."

name: Mausoleum Turnkey
text: When Mausoleum Turnkey enters the battlefield, return target creature card of an opponent's choice from your graveyard to your hand.
flavor: When he reaches for his key ring, you should be running for the exit.

name: Moonlight Bargain
text: Look at the top five cards of your library. For each card, put that card into your graveyard unless you pay 2 life. Then put the rest into your hand.
flavor: At every fifth full moon, the Moon Market convenes to peddle Ravnica's most forbidden wares.

name: Mortipede
text: {2}{G}: All creatures able to block Mortipede this turn do so.
flavor: Mortipede pheromones choke the streets with sickly sweetness, luring the rash and unwary into its waiting jaws.

name: Necromantic Thirst
text: Enchant creature\nWhenever enchanted creature deals combat damage to a player, you may return target creature card from your graveyard to your hand.

name: Necroplasm
text: At the beginning of your upkeep, put a +1/+1 counter on Necroplasm.\nAt the beginning of your end step, destroy each creature with converted mana cost equal to the number of +1/+1 counters on Necroplasm.\nDredge 2 (If you would draw a card, instead you may put exactly two cards from the top of your library into your graveyard. If you do, return this card from your graveyard to your hand. Otherwise, draw a card.)

name: Netherborn Phalanx
text: When Netherborn Phalanx enters the battlefield, each opponent loses 1 life for each creature he or she controls.\nTransmute {1}{B}{B} ({1}{B}{B}, Discard this card: Search your library for a card with the same converted mana cost as this card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then shuffle your library. Transmute only as a sorcery.)

name: Nightmare Void
text: Target player reveals his or her hand. You choose a card from it. That player discards that card.\nDredge 2 (If you would draw a card, instead you may put exactly two cards from the top of your library into your graveyard. If you do, return this card from your graveyard to your hand. Otherwise, draw a card.)

name: Ribbons of Night
text: Ribbons of Night deals 4 damage to target creature and you gain 4 life. If {U} was spent to cast Ribbons of Night, draw a card.
flavor: "My favorite meal is angel's flesh, slain in agony and iced with black vinegar."\n—Aszala of House Dimir

name: Roofstalker Wight
text: {1}{U}: Roofstalker Wight gains flying until end of turn.
flavor: No heartbeat to hear, no greed to bribe, no fear of death.

name: Sadistic Augermage
text: When Sadistic Augermage dies, each player puts a card from his or her hand on top of his or her library.
flavor: "Don't worry. I know the drill."

name: Sewerdreg
text: Swampwalk (This creature can't be blocked as long as defending player controls a Swamp.)\nSacrifice Sewerdreg: Exile target card from a graveyard.
flavor: They hardly have form, dripping through pipe and grate with the slip and stench of flowing sewage.

name: Shred Memory
text: Exile up to four target cards from a single graveyard.\nTransmute {1}{B}{B} ({1}{B}{B}, Discard this card: Search your library for a card with the same converted mana cost as this card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then shuffle your library. Transmute only as a sorcery.)

name: Sins of the Past
text: Until end of turn, you may cast target instant or sorcery card from your graveyard without paying its mana cost. If that card would be put into your graveyard this turn, exile it instead. Exile Sins of the Past.

name: Stinkweed Imp
text: Flying\nWhenever Stinkweed Imp deals combat damage to a creature, destroy that creature.\nDredge 5 (If you would draw a card, instead you may put exactly five cards from the top of your library into your graveyard. If you do, return this card from your graveyard to your hand. Otherwise, draw a card.)

name: Strands of Undeath
text: Enchant creature\nWhen Strands of Undeath enters the battlefield, target player discards two cards.\n{B}: Regenerate enchanted creature.
flavor: "Why limit yourself to mortal law when you can outlive those who enforce it?"\n—Czaric, Orzhov prelate

name: Thoughtpicker Witch
text: {1}, Sacrifice a creature: Look at the top two cards of target opponent's library, then exile one of them.
flavor: "Once the brew gets the brains nice and pickled, they're a lot easier to pick through."

name: Undercity Shade
text: Fear (This creature can't be blocked except by artifact creatures and/or black creatures.)\n{B}: Undercity Shade gets +1/+1 until end of turn.
flavor: "Officially, there's nothing under that bridge to hunt . . . Unofficially, my torchers are too terrified to go there after nightfall."\n—Agrus Kos

name: Vigor Mortis
text: Return target creature card from your graveyard to the battlefield. If {G} was spent to cast Vigor Mortis, that creature enters the battlefield with an additional +1/+1 counter on it.
flavor: After fear and weakness rot away, that which remains is stronger than its living form.

name: Vindictive Mob
text: When Vindictive Mob enters the battlefield, sacrifice a creature.\nVindictive Mob can't be blocked by Saprolings.
flavor: Many minds, a single madness.

name: Woebringer Demon
text: Flying\nAt the beginning of each player's upkeep, that player sacrifices a creature. If the player can't, sacrifice Woebringer Demon.
flavor: Each soul he devours adds its hunger to his own.

name: Barbarian Riftcutter
text: {R}, Sacrifice Barbarian Riftcutter: Destroy target land.
flavor: "Riftcutters are suicidal anarchists, waving those lightning axes around so much that the walls are as likely to fall as their foes."\n—Heruj, Selesnya initiate

name: Blockbuster
text: {1}{R}, Sacrifice Blockbuster: Blockbuster deals 3 damage to each tapped creature and each player.
flavor: Vendors hung cords heavy with roots and laid out boxes of salted meat, unaware of the fiery disaster swiftly approaching.

name: Breath of Fury
text: Enchant creature you control\nWhen enchanted creature deals combat damage to a player, sacrifice it and attach Breath of Fury to a creature you control. If you do, untap all creatures you control and after this phase, there is an additional combat phase.

name: Char
text: Char deals 4 damage to target creature or player and 2 damage to you.
flavor: Izzet mages often acquire their magic reagents from dubious sources, so the potency of their spells is never predictable.

name: Cleansing Beam
text: Radiance — Cleansing Beam deals 2 damage to target creature and each other creature that shares a color with it.
flavor: "Justice is toothless without punishment. Righteousness cannot succeed without the suffering of the guilty."\n—Razia

name: Coalhauler Swine
text: Whenever Coalhauler Swine is dealt damage, it deals that much damage to each player.
flavor: Nothing stops industry in Ravnica—certainly not the safety of its workers.

name: Dogpile
text: Dogpile deals damage to target creature or player equal to the number of attacking creatures you control.
flavor: There is no shelter from this storm, its rain of fists, or the thunderous cackles of bloodlust.

name: Excruciator
text: Damage that would be dealt by Excruciator can't be prevented.
flavor: "Though used as a piercing weapon, the tusk is more akin to a stinger, spreading pain instantly throughout the body of its victim. This specimen deserves further study."\n—Simic research notes

name: Fiery Conclusion
text: As an additional cost to cast Fiery Conclusion, sacrifice a creature.\nFiery Conclusion deals 5 damage to target creature.
flavor: The Boros legionnaire saw a noble sacrifice, the Rakdos thug a blazing suicide, and the Izzet alchemist an experiment gone awry.

name: Flame Fusillade
text: Until end of turn, permanents you control gain "{T}: This permanent deals 1 damage to target creature or player."
flavor: "A single item acting as lantern and lance? Now that's military efficiency."\n—Brev Grezar, Boros lieutenant

name: Flash Conscription
text: Untap target creature and gain control of it until end of turn.  That creature gains haste until end of turn. If {W} was spent to cast Flash Conscription, the creature gains "Whenever this creature deals combat damage, you gain that much life" until end of turn.

name: Frenzied Goblin
text: Whenever Frenzied Goblin attacks, you may pay {R}. If you do, target creature can't block this turn.
flavor: The upside to not thinking about the consequences is that you'll always surprise those who do.

name: Galvanic Arc
text: Enchant creature\nWhen Galvanic Arc enters the battlefield, it deals 3 damage to target creature or player.\nEnchanted creature has first strike.

name: Goblin Fire Fiend
text: Haste\nGoblin Fire Fiend must be blocked if able.\n{R}: Goblin Fire Fiend gets +1/+0 until end of turn.

name: Goblin Spelunkers
text: Mountainwalk (This creature can't be blocked as long as defending player controls a Mountain.)
flavor: Chimney sweeps, explorers of abandoned buildings, spire climbers . . . goblin spelunkers have found countless niches within Ravnica's metropolis.

name: Greater Forgeling
text: {1}{R}: Greater Forgeling gets +3/-3 until end of turn.
flavor: Few have seen the inner workings of Ravnica's furnaces, but neighboring districts catch brief glimpses in the horrors that escape the flames.

name: Hammerfist Giant
text: {T}: Hammerfist Giant deals 4 damage to each creature without flying and each player.
flavor: "Oh sure, they buy a lot of ale, but I always find myself needing to rebuild after the giants have paid a visit."\n—Belko, owner of Titan's Keg tavern

name: Hunted Dragon
text: Flying, haste\nWhen Hunted Dragon enters the battlefield, target opponent puts three 2/2 white Knight creature tokens with first strike onto the battlefield.
flavor: The knights see a mighty quarry. The dragon sees breakfast, lunch, and dinner.

name: Incite Hysteria
text: Radiance — Until end of turn, target creature and each other creature that shares a color with it gain "This creature can't block."
flavor: "The Boros say they want to bring order to Ravnica. Funny then, how well they use chaos."\n—Trigori, Azorius senator

name: Indentured Oaf
text: Prevent all damage that Indentured Oaf would deal to red creatures.
flavor: All it knows is the difference between friend and food.

name: Instill Furor
text: Enchant creature\nEnchanted creature has "At the beginning of your end step, sacrifice this creature unless it attacked this turn."
flavor: "The Rakdos know little of technology, but they definitely know how to push buttons."\n—Trivaz, Izzet mage

name: Mindmoil
text: Whenever you cast a spell, put the cards in your hand on the bottom of your library in any order, then draw that many cards.
flavor: "My criticism of the Izzet is that their impulse for learning seems too much like impulse and too little like learning."\n—Trigori, Azorius senator

name: Molten Sentry
text: As Molten Sentry enters the battlefield, flip a coin. If the coin comes up heads, Molten Sentry enters the battlefield as a 5/2 creature with haste. If it comes up tails, Molten Sentry enters the battlefield as a 2/5 creature with defender.
flavor: Some take after their father, Stone, some after their mother, Fire.

name: Ordruun Commando
text: {W}: Prevent the next 1 damage that would be dealt to Ordruun Commando this turn.
flavor: Thick of muscle, stout of heart, and possessing a burning love of justice and the battlefield, the Ordruun minotaurs are the foundation of the Boros Legion.

name: Rain of Embers
text: Rain of Embers deals 1 damage to each creature and each player.
flavor: There's plenty to talk about in the marketplaces of Ravnica, be it the latest feud between guilds or the terrible weather.

name: Reroute
text: Change the target of target activated ability with a single target. (Mana abilities can't be targeted.)\nDraw a card.
flavor: Three hundred years of practice thwarted by an instant of mischief.

name: Sabertooth Alley Cat
text: Sabertooth Alley Cat attacks each turn if able.\n{1}{R}: Creatures without defender can't block Sabertooth Alley Cat this turn.
flavor: It has eight lives' worth of hunger to satisfy.

name: Seismic Spike
text: Destroy target land. Add {R}{R} to your mana pool.
flavor: Natural disasters in Ravnica are largely nullified by the Izzet. Unnatural disasters, on the other hand, happen all of the time.

name: Sell-Sword Brute
text: When Sell-Sword Brute dies, it deals 2 damage to you.
flavor: "Killing is easy. Just wrap your hand around the haft, and wrap your enemy around the blade."

name: Smash
text: Destroy target artifact.\nDraw a card.
flavor: Ravnica's laws protect not its citizens but its industry. Aging equipment is destroyed rather than restored, to bring more money into the factories' coffers.

name: Sparkmage Apprentice
text: When Sparkmage Apprentice enters the battlefield, it deals 1 damage to target creature or player.
flavor: Pajik was amazed and pleased at his newfound powers. His pet cat Rivin was slightly less enthusiastic.

name: Stoneshaker Shaman
text: At the beginning of each player's end step, that player sacrifices an untapped land.
flavor: There is no place in Ravnica for stagnation, no room for lands unfilled and untilled.

name: Surge of Zeal
text: Radiance — Target creature and each other creature that shares a color with it gain haste until end of turn.
flavor: "If only my poxes were as infectious as their zealotry."\n—Savra

name: Torpid Moloch
text: Defender (This creature can't attack.)\nSacrifice three lands: Torpid Moloch loses defender until end of turn.
flavor: Market hucksters sell molochs for use as watchdogs. Of course, that's all molochs do. Sit around . . . and watch.

name: Viashino Fangtail
text: {T}: Viashino Fangtail deals 1 damage to target creature or player.
flavor: "When the bony terminus gets too large, it's shed from the tail in coinciding periods of heightened aggression and hunger."\n—Simic research notes

name: Viashino Slasher
text: {R}: Viashino Slasher gets +1/-1 until end of turn.
flavor: Citizens of Ravnica stick to the main streets. Shortcuts may look tempting, but down each alley, dozens of hungry hands await, and screams do not carry into the busy market throng.

name: Warp World
text: Each player shuffles all permanents he or she owns into his or her library, then reveals that many cards from the top of his or her library. Each player puts all artifact, creature, and land cards revealed this way onto the battlefield, then does the same for enchantment cards, then puts all cards revealed this way that weren't put onto the battlefield on the bottom of his or her library.

name: War-Torch Goblin
text: {R}, Sacrifice War-Torch Goblin: War-Torch Goblin deals 2 damage to target blocking creature.
flavor: "In a town shaped by the subtle machinations and political intrigue of its guilds, it's reassuring to see a goblin waving his torch and screaming about some nonsense or other."\n—Agrus Kos

name: Wojek Embermage
text: Radiance — {T}: Wojek Embermage deals 1 damage to target creature and each other creature that shares a color with it.
flavor: "Your brother's crimes are your crimes. You stood by and lent support, so you too must face judgment."

name: Birds of Paradise
text: Flying\n{T}: Add one mana of any color to your mana pool.
flavor: Long ago, birds of paradise littered the skies. Thanks to the city's sprawl, most now exist as pets of society's elite.

name: Bramble Elemental
text: Whenever an Aura becomes attached to Bramble Elemental, put two 1/1 green Saproling creature tokens onto the battlefield.
flavor: Ravnica is a seamless urban tapestry, each city bleeding into the next. In abandoned corners, however, nature has begun to reclaim what it once owned.

name: Carven Caryatid
text: Defender (This creature can't attack.)\nWhen Carven Caryatid enters the battlefield, draw a card.
flavor: So-called "old wood" is rare in deforested Ravnica. Statues carved from it are said to house the last of the ancient nature spirits.

name: Chord of Calling
text: Convoke (Your creatures can help cast this spell. Each creature you tap while casting this spell pays for {1} or one mana of that creature's color.)\nSearch your library for a creature card with converted mana cost X or less and put it onto the battlefield. Then shuffle your library.

name: Civic Wayfinder
text: When Civic Wayfinder enters the battlefield, you may search your library for a basic land card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. If you do, shuffle your library.
flavor: "These alleys are not safe. Come, I can guide you back to the market square."

name: Doubling Season
text: If an effect would put one or more tokens onto the battlefield under your control, it puts twice that many of those tokens onto the battlefield instead.\nIf an effect would place one or more counters on a permanent you control, it places twice that many of those counters on that permanent instead.

name: Dowsing Shaman
text: {2}{G}, {T}: Return target enchantment card from your graveyard to your hand.
flavor: He combs the streets looking for the lost light, the discarded enigmas of the city.

name: Dryad's Caress
text: You gain 1 life for each creature on the battlefield. If {W} was spent to cast Dryad's Caress, untap all creatures you control.
flavor: "I awoke to the face of beauty, my body fully healed. In that moment I knew my destiny was the Conclave's to shape."\n—Rogad, Selesnya initiate

name: Elves of Deep Shadow
text: {T}: Add {B} to your mana pool. Elves of Deep Shadow deals 1 damage to you.
flavor: Cast out of the Conclave generations ago, these elves found a home in the corrupted districts of the Golgari.

name: Elvish Skysweeper
text: {4}{G}, Sacrifice a creature: Destroy target creature with flying.
flavor: The spires of Ravnica are no different from the tall trees of other planes. The elves navigate and protect them just the same.

name: Farseek
text: Search your library for a Plains, Island, Swamp, or Mountain card and put it onto the battlefield tapped. Then shuffle your library.
flavor: "How truly vast this city must be, that I have traveled so far and seen so much, yet never once found the place where the buildings fail."

name: Fists of Ironwood
text: Enchant creature\nWhen Fists of Ironwood enters the battlefield, put two 1/1 green Saproling creature tokens onto the battlefield.\nEnchanted creature has trample.
flavor: Saprolings add the three and the four to the "one-two punch."

name: Gather Courage
text: Convoke (Your creatures can help cast this spell. Each creature you tap while casting this spell pays for {1} or one mana of that creature's color.)\nTarget creature gets +2/+2 until end of turn.

name: Golgari Brownscale
text: When Golgari Brownscale is put into your hand from your graveyard, you gain 2 life.\nDredge 2 (If you would draw a card, instead you may put exactly two cards from the top of your library into your graveyard. If you do, return this card from your graveyard to your hand. Otherwise, draw a card.)

name: Golgari Grave-Troll
text: Golgari Grave-Troll enters the battlefield with a +1/+1 counter on it for each creature card in your graveyard.\n{1}, Remove a +1/+1 counter from Golgari Grave-Troll: Regenerate Golgari Grave-Troll.\nDredge 6 (If you would draw a card, instead you may put exactly six cards from the top of your library into your graveyard. If you do, return this card from your graveyard to your hand. Otherwise, draw a card.)

name: Goliath Spider
text: Reach (This creature can block creatures with flying.)
flavor: The glittering strands of its complex web catch everything from a buzzing gnat to a passing bloatdrake.

name: Greater Mossdog
text: Dredge 3 (If you would draw a card, instead you may put exactly three cards from the top of your library into your graveyard. If you do, return this card from your graveyard to your hand. Otherwise, draw a card.)
flavor: Man's best fungus.

name: Hunted Troll
text: When Hunted Troll enters the battlefield, target opponent puts four 1/1 blue Faerie creature tokens with flying onto the battlefield.\n{G}: Regenerate Hunted Troll.

name: Ivy Dancer
text: {T}: Target creature gains forestwalk until end of turn. (It can't be blocked as long as defending player controls a Forest.)
flavor: Her ivy locks are a remnant of the wooded wilds now lost to Ravnica forever.

name: Life from the Loam
text: Return up to three target land cards from your graveyard to your hand.\nDredge 3 (If you would draw a card, instead you may put exactly three cards from the top of your library into your graveyard. If you do, return this card from your graveyard to your hand. Otherwise, draw a card.)

name: Moldervine Cloak
text: Enchant creature\nEnchanted creature gets +3/+3.\nDredge 2 (If you would draw a card, instead you may put exactly two cards from the top of your library into your graveyard. If you do, return this card from your graveyard to your hand. Otherwise, draw a card.)

name: Nullmage Shepherd
text: Tap four untapped creatures you control: Destroy target artifact or enchantment.
flavor: The shepherds work in secret, seeking out abominations against nature and returning them to earth and dust.

name: Overwhelm
text: Convoke (Your creatures can help cast this spell. Each creature you tap while casting this spell pays for {1} or one mana of that creature's color.)\nCreatures you control get +3/+3 until end of turn.
flavor: "Let the song of Selesnya be heard above the rhythm of our thundering hordes!"

name: Perilous Forays
text: {1}, Sacrifice a creature: Search your library for a land card with a basic land type and put it onto the battlefield tapped. Then shuffle your library.
flavor: "This is the place? This map has got to be wrong . . . ."\n—Svania Trul, wayfinder novice, last words

name: Primordial Sage
text: Whenever you cast a creature spell, you may draw a card.
flavor: For each creature that arrives in its audience, the sage imparts another piece of ancient wisdom for all to hear.

name: Recollect
text: Return target card from your graveyard to your hand.
flavor: "The bones of the past will tell their tales—if you know how to speak their language."\n—Savra

name: Rolling Spoil
text: Destroy target land. If {B} was spent to cast Rolling Spoil, all creatures get -1/-1 until end of turn.
flavor: The shadow that fell over the grove was silent yet horribly alive, roiling with millions of tiny minions dedicated to the process of rot.

name: Root-Kin Ally
text: Convoke (Your creatures can help cast this spell. Each creature you tap while casting this spell pays for {1} or one mana of that creature's color.)\nTap two untapped creatures you control: Root-Kin Ally gets +2/+2 until end of turn.

name: Scatter the Seeds
text: Convoke (Your creatures can help cast this spell. Each creature you tap while casting this spell pays for {1} or one mana of that creature's color.)\nPut three 1/1 green Saproling creature tokens onto the battlefield.
flavor: From the seeds of faith, great forests grow.

name: Scion of the Wild
text: Scion of the Wild's power and toughness are each equal to the number of creatures you control.
flavor: It has a hundred thousand extinctions to avenge.

name: Siege Wurm
text: Convoke (Your creatures can help cast this spell. Each creature you tap while casting this spell pays for {1} or one mana of that creature's color.)\nTrample (This creature can deal excess combat damage to defending player or planeswalker while attacking.)
flavor: The Rubblefield was once among the wealthiest districts in Ravnica. All it took was a single wurm to reduce it to ruins.

name: Stone-Seeder Hierophant
text: Whenever a land enters the battlefield under your control, untap Stone-Seeder Hierophant.\n{T}: Untap target land.
flavor: Her touch brings to bare stone what water and sun bring to rich soil.

name: Sundering Vitae
text: Convoke (Your creatures can help cast this spell. Each creature you tap while casting this spell pays for {1} or one mana of that creature's color.)\nDestroy target artifact or enchantment.
flavor: Centuries of wind, rain, and roots compressed into an instant of destruction: such is the power of Selesnya.

name: Transluminant
text: {W}, Sacrifice Transluminant: Put a 1/1 white Spirit creature token with flying onto the battlefield at the beginning of the next end step.
flavor: "Forget yourself. Forget your city. Forget your homes, your families, the debts and obligations that hold you to this world."

name: Trophy Hunter
text: {1}{G}: Trophy Hunter deals 1 damage to target creature with flying.\nWhenever a creature with flying dealt damage by Trophy Hunter this turn dies, put a +1/+1 counter on Trophy Hunter.

name: Ursapine
text: {G}: Target creature gets +1/+1 until end of turn.
flavor: A friendly ursapine means a constant supply of sharp spears. An unfriendly one means a constant supply of small holes.

name: Vinelasher Kudzu
text: Whenever a land enters the battlefield under your control, put a +1/+1 counter on Vinelasher Kudzu.
flavor: It grows to hate you.

name: Agrus Kos, Wojek Veteran
text: Whenever Agrus Kos, Wojek Veteran attacks, attacking red creatures get +2/+0 and attacking white creatures get +0/+2 until end of turn.
flavor: Lieutenant Kos has never met a group of recruits he could not inspire or a mob he could not quell.

name: Autochthon Wurm
text: Convoke (Your creatures can help cast this spell. Each creature you tap while casting this spell pays for {1} or one mana of that creature's color.)\nTrample
flavor: The trainer awoke to begin the journey from the wurm's tail to its head. The sun was setting when she arrived.

name: Bloodbond March
text: Whenever a player casts a creature spell, each player returns all cards with the same name as that spell from his or her graveyard to the battlefield.
flavor: The Golgari support a vast army because death never ends its soldiers' service.

name: Boros Swiftblade
text: Double strike
flavor: When the Boros Legion attacks, swiftblades enter the fray first. They pick off the archers and mages, softening the enemy front before the flame-kin and giants go in.

name: Brightflame
text: Radiance — Brightflame deals X damage to target creature and each other creature that shares a color with it. You gain life equal to the damage dealt this way.
flavor: "Let the pyres of the unbelievers light our way."\n—Razia

name: Chorus of the Conclave
text: Forestwalk (This creature can't be blocked as long as defending player controls a Forest.)\nAs an additional cost to cast creature spells, you may pay any amount of mana. If you do, that creature enters the battlefield with that many additional +1/+1 counters on it.
flavor: "We are many, yet one. We are separate in body, yet speak with a single voice. Join us in our chorus."

name: Circu, Dimir Lobotomist
text: Whenever you cast a blue spell, exile the top card of target library.\nWhenever you cast a black spell, exile the top card of target library.\nYour opponents can't cast nonland cards with the same name as a card exiled with Circu, Dimir Lobotomist.

name: Clutch of the Undercity
text: Return target permanent to its owner's hand. Its controller loses 3 life.\nTransmute {1}{U}{B} ({1}{U}{B}, Discard this card: Search your library for a card with the same converted mana cost as this card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then shuffle your library. Transmute only as a sorcery.)

name: Congregation at Dawn
text: Search your library for up to three creature cards and reveal them. Shuffle your library, then put those cards on top of it in any order.
flavor: "It is fitting that we meet in the first hour of light, for we are called by the Conclave to pierce a threat of darkness."

name: Consult the Necrosages
text: Choose one —\n• Target player draws two cards.\n• Target player discards two cards.
flavor: Dimir rank and file never see nor hear their guildmaster. All orders are given through mysterious necrosages who appear from the shadows, tersely toss out a command, and then melt into the darkness.

name: Dark Heart of the Wood
text: Sacrifice a Forest: You gain 3 life.
flavor: "The soil here is rich with the rotting dead, and the sun's fingers barely penetrate the dark canopy. Plant our brethren here. This shall be our sanctuary."\n—Savra

name: Dimir Cutpurse
text: Whenever Dimir Cutpurse deals combat damage to a player, that player discards a card and you draw a card.
flavor: Other guilds demand tolls from those who travel their territories, but not House Dimir. It takes its share secretly, one coin purse at a time.

name: Dimir Doppelganger
text: {1}{U}{B}: Exile target creature card from a graveyard. Dimir Doppelganger becomes a copy of that card and gains this ability.
flavor: "Fear not. Your life will not go unlived."

name: Dimir Infiltrator
text: Dimir Infiltrator can't be blocked.\nTransmute {1}{U}{B} ({1}{U}{B}, Discard this card: Search your library for a card with the same converted mana cost as this card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then shuffle your library. Transmute only as a sorcery.)

name: Drooling Groodion
text: {2}{B}{G}, Sacrifice a creature: Target creature gets +2/+2 until end of turn. Another target creature gets -2/-2 until end of turn.
flavor: "The Golgari expand, yes, but I refuse to call their tainted creations ‘growth.'"\n—Veszka, Selesnya evangel

name: Firemane Angel
text: Flying, first strike\nAt the beginning of your upkeep, if Firemane Angel is in your graveyard or on the battlefield, you may gain 1 life.\n{6}{R}{R}{W}{W}: Return Firemane Angel from your graveyard to the battlefield. Activate this ability only during your upkeep.

name: Flame-Kin Zealot
text: When Flame-Kin Zealot enters the battlefield, creatures you control get +1/+1 and gain haste until end of turn.
flavor: Boros soldiers are like a cache of bombs ready to explode, and the flame-kin light their fuses.

name: Glare of Subdual
text: Tap an untapped creature you control: Tap target artifact or creature.
flavor: The righteous light of Selesnya is channeled through the devout, striking out to blind the nonbelievers.

name: Glimpse the Unthinkable
text: Target player puts the top ten cards of his or her library into his or her graveyard.
flavor: "I am confident that if anyone actually penetrates our facades, even the most perceptive would still be fundamentally unprepared for the truth of House Dimir."\n—Szadek

name: Golgari Germination
text: Whenever a nontoken creature you control dies, put a 1/1 green Saproling creature token onto the battlefield.
flavor: The Golgari don't bury their dead. They plant them.

name: Golgari Rotwurm
text: {B}, Sacrifice a creature: Target player loses 1 life.
flavor: Like corpse-worms through a carapace, rotwurms slide through the hollowed bones of the undercity.

name: Grave-Shell Scarab
text: {1}, Sacrifice Grave-Shell Scarab: Draw a card.\nDredge 1 (If you would draw a card, instead you may put exactly one card from the top of your library into your graveyard. If you do, return this card from your graveyard to your hand. Otherwise, draw a card.)

name: Guardian of Vitu-Ghazi
text: Convoke (Your creatures can help cast this spell. Each creature you tap while casting this spell pays for {1} or one mana of that creature's color.)\nVigilance
flavor: It stands sentinel to the great City-Tree, home of the Selesnya Conclave.

name: Lightning Helix
text: Lightning Helix deals 3 damage to target creature or player and you gain 3 life.
flavor: Though less well-known than its army of soldiers, the Boros Legion's mage-priests are as respected by the innocent as they are hated by the ghosts of the guilty.

name: Loxodon Hierarch
text: When Loxodon Hierarch enters the battlefield, you gain 4 life.\n{G}{W}, Sacrifice Loxodon Hierarch: Regenerate each creature you control.
flavor: "I have lived long, and I remember how this city once was. If my death serves to bring back the Ravnica in my memory, then so be it."

name: Mindleech Mass
text: Trample\nWhenever Mindleech Mass deals combat damage to a player, you may look at that player's hand. If you do, you may cast a nonland card in it without paying that card's mana cost.

name: Moroii
text: Flying\nAt the beginning of your upkeep, you lose 1 life.
flavor: "Touched by moroii"\n—Undercity slang meaning "to grow old"

name: Perplex
text: Counter target spell unless its controller discards his or her hand.\nTransmute {1}{U}{B} ({1}{U}{B}, Discard this card: Search your library for a card with the same converted mana cost as this card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then shuffle your library. Transmute only as a sorcery.)

name: Phytohydra
text: If damage would be dealt to Phytohydra, put that many +1/+1 counters on it instead.
flavor: "Look at this creature, so like the Conclave it serves. Cut one head and it grows two. Damage it and it flourishes."\n—Veszka, Selesnya evangel

name: Pollenbright Wings
text: Enchant creature\nEnchanted creature has flying.\nWhenever enchanted creature deals combat damage to a player, put that many 1/1 green Saproling creature tokens onto the battlefield.

name: Psychic Drain
text: Target player puts the top X cards of his or her library into his or her graveyard and you gain X life.
flavor: "Gold can be reearned, goods restored. The moroii steal youth, more precious than either, and once gone, it's gone forever."\n—Berta Suszat, civic healer

name: Putrefy
text: Destroy target artifact or creature. It can't be regenerated.
flavor: "All matter, animate or not, rots when exposed to time. We merely speed up the process."\n—Ezoc, Golgari rot farmer

name: Rally the Righteous
text: Radiance — Untap target creature and each other creature that shares a color with it. Those creatures get +2/+0 until end of turn.
flavor: Yuri took up the ragged Boros banner, and his brethren, inspired by the act, followed him back into the fight.

name: Razia, Boros Archangel
text: Flying, vigilance, haste\n{T}: The next 3 damage that would be dealt to target creature you control this turn is dealt to another target creature instead.
flavor: Her sword burns with such brightness that foes avert their eyes and arrows divert their paths.

name: Razia's Purification
text: Each player chooses three permanents he or she controls, then sacrifices the rest.
flavor: Only the chosen ones are spared.

name: Savra, Queen of the Golgari
text: Whenever you sacrifice a black creature, you may pay 2 life. If you do, each other player sacrifices a creature.\nWhenever you sacrifice a green creature, you may gain 2 life.
flavor: "Nature's most raw beauty is the circle: perfect in its continuance, with no break between death and life."

name: Searing Meditation
text: Whenever you gain life, you may pay {2}. If you do, Searing Meditation deals 2 damage to target creature or player.
flavor: "When I meditate I see the world as it should be. All that does not fit, I remove."\n—Alovnek, Boros guildmage

name: Seeds of Strength
text: Target creature gets +1/+1 until end of turn.\nTarget creature gets +1/+1 until end of turn.\nTarget creature gets +1/+1 until end of turn.
flavor: Beneath the beauty of light and seed is the might of Vitu-Ghazi.

name: Selesnya Evangel
text: {1}, {T}, Tap an untapped creature you control: Put a 1/1 green Saproling creature token onto the battlefield.
flavor: "The clamor of the city drowns all voices. But together we can sing a harmony that will resonate from Ravnica's tallest spires to her deepest wells."

name: Selesnya Sagittars
text: Reach (This creature can block creatures with flying.)\nSelesnya Sagittars can block an additional creature each combat.
flavor: "What's their strike range, you ask? Let's put it this way: sagittars aim their bows using maps."\n—Otak, Tin Street shopkeep

name: Shambling Shell
text: Sacrifice Shambling Shell: Put a +1/+1 counter on target creature.\nDredge 3 (If you would draw a card, instead you may put exactly three cards from the top of your library into your graveyard. If you do, return this card from your graveyard to your hand. Otherwise, draw a card.)

name: Sisters of Stone Death
text: {G}: Target creature blocks Sisters of Stone Death this turn if able.\n{B}{G}: Exile target creature blocking or blocked by Sisters of Stone Death.\n{2}{B}: Put a creature card exiled with Sisters of Stone Death onto the battlefield under your control.

name: Skyknight Legionnaire
text: Flying, haste
flavor: "I do not know which gives me more pride: the legions of soldiers marching in thunderous lockstep, or the cry of the skyknights riding their rocs like jagged lightning overhead."\n—Razia

name: Sunhome Enforcer
text: Whenever Sunhome Enforcer deals combat damage, you gain that much life.\n{1}{R}: Sunhome Enforcer gets +1/+0 until end of turn.
flavor: "Law soothed his savage heart. Where fury once burned, the enduring flame of order now shines."\n—Razia

name: Szadek, Lord of Secrets
text: Flying\nIf Szadek, Lord of Secrets would deal combat damage to a player, instead put that many +1/+1 counters on Szadek and that player puts that many cards from the top of his or her library into his or her graveyard.

name: Thundersong Trumpeter
text: {T}: Target creature can't attack or block this turn.
flavor: "Hear that? Those notes mean we've arrived at Sunhome! Let our allies' hearts soar and our enemies' hearts shatter at the sound!"\n—Klattic, Boros legionnaire

name: Tolsimir Wolfblood
text: Other green creatures you control get +1/+1.\nOther white creatures you control get +1/+1.\n{T}: Put a legendary 2/2 green and white Wolf creature token named Voja onto the battlefield.

name: Twisted Justice
text: Target player sacrifices a creature. You draw cards equal to that creature's power.
flavor: In Otiev's mind, he ruled in favor of the accused. But in his courtroom he was only a spectator, watching his hand deliver the sign of death.

name: Vulturous Zombie
text: Flying\nWhenever a card is put into an opponent's graveyard from anywhere, put a +1/+1 counter on Vulturous Zombie.
flavor: "When something dies, all things benefit. Well okay, just our things."\n—Ezoc, Golgari rot farmer

name: Watchwolf
flavor: Only in Ravnica do the wolves watch the flock.

name: Woodwraith Corrupter
text: {1}{B}{G}, {T}: Target Forest becomes a 4/4 black and green Elemental Horror creature. It's still a land.
flavor: "Its darkened sap penetrates natural fibers and spreads its own genes. Emulation experiments are underway."\n—Simic research notes

name: Woodwraith Strangler
text: Exile a creature card from your graveyard: Regenerate Woodwraith Strangler.
flavor: "Nothing could be more natural than roots sucking nourishment from the dead."\n—Savra

name: Boros Guildmage

name: Boros Recruit
text: ({R/W} can be paid with either {R} or {W}.)\nFirst strike
flavor: "Look at this goblin, once wild, untamed, and full of idiocy. The Boros have given him the skill of a soldier and focused his heart with a single cause."\n—Razia

name: Centaur Safeguard
text: ({G/W} can be paid with either {G} or {W}.)\nWhen Centaur Safeguard dies, you may gain 3 life.
flavor: Swift, strong, and selfless, the centaurs are the shields of the Conclave.

name: Dimir Signet
text: {1}, {T}: Add {U}{B} to your mana pool.
flavor: An emblem of a secret guild, the Dimir insignia is seen only by its own members—and the doomed.

name: Glass Golem
flavor: Izzet artificers have learned to steer their beautiful constructs clear of Boros warhammers—and the opera house.

name: Golgari Signet
text: {1}, {T}: Add {B}{G} to your mana pool.
flavor: Depending on your point of view, the seal represents a proud guardian of the natural cycle or one who has sold her soul to darkness for eternal life.

name: Selesnya Signet
text: {1}, {T}: Add {G}{W} to your mana pool.
